                    "process": "G",
                    "product": ""
                  }
                }
              },
              "free_text": [
                "     Radiative capture photons are",
                "compton scattered from a curved aluminium plate. The",
                "energy of scattered photons was easily varied by",
                "rotating and bending the scattering plate."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "the targets of U-238 (enriched to 99.97%, 7.77",
                "mg/cm**2) and U-235 (enriched to 97.68%, 7.25",
                "mg/cm**2) were the cylindrical metal foil targets",
                "5.08 cm high and 2.22 cm diameter."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "EXTB"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                ""
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "SOLST"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Heavy-ion surface barrier detectors.",
                "The experimental yield curves were measured using four",
                " detectors were mounted at 45 and 135 degrees with",
                " respect to the incident photon beam."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "PART-DET": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "FF"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                ""
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ANALYSIS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "INTAD",
                "UNFLD",
                "LEAST"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The net yield curve was obtained",
                " by normalization of the raw yield data followed by",
                " background substraction from the total photofission",
                " yield.",
                "The average photofission cross section was determined",
                " by unfolding the beam spectra from the net",
                " photofission yield curve using the least-structure",
                " method. Applying the appropriate target, counting",
                " efficiency, and normalization factors to the average",
                " cross section, the absolute cross cross section value",
                " were obtained."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ERR-ANALYS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "heading": "DATA-ERR",
                "minimum_value": null,
                "maximum_value": null,
                "correlation_property": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                "  The errors are the uncertainties due to",
                "propagation of the yield point statistical errors",
                "through the unfolding equations. The systematic errors",
                "were estimated to be about 30%."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "COMMENT": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Cross sections extracted from measured yield curves",
                "are reported for photofission of U-238 and U-235.",
                "The monoenergetic photons were obtained by compton",
                "scattering g-rays produced by neutron capture in a",
                "nickel plate near the core of the 5 mw ames",
                "laboratory research reactor. An unfolding procedure",
                "was used to extract the smoothed cross sections from",
                "the measured yield curves. In the U-238(g,f) cross",
                "section, prominent structure is observed at 6.2 MeV",
                "and 7.6 MeV with hints of structure at 5.5 MeV and",
                "7.0 MeV. The U-235(g,f) cross section shows",
                "pronounced structure at 5.9 MeV, 6.6 MeV, and 7.5",
                "MeV with a hint of structure at 5.4 MeV."
              ]
            }
          ],
